awd_titl_txt: Organometallic Complexes of the Iron Triad Metal with       Nitrido, Imido, Oxo, or Sulfido Ligands
awd_abstract_narration: 9308450  Shapley  This project, supported by the Inorganic, Bioinorganic and  Organometallic Chemistry Program, is concerned with the  synthesis and reactivity of high oxidation state Fe, Ru, and Os  complexes.  A major focus will be on new complexes that contain  two multiply bonded ligands (oxo, sulfido, imido), which are  expected to be effective for atom (O, S) or group (NR) transfer  to unsaturated hydrocarbons.  Also to be investigated are  coordinatively unsaturated ruthenium based olefin  polymerization catalysts, unique chromium-osmium  heterobimetallic oxidation catalysts and their use in kinetic  resolution of alcohols, and novel high oxidation state  organoiron derivatives.  %%%  This project focusses on the design and synthesis of new  transition metal containing molecules that are predicted to  have unique, and potentially useful, chemical reactivities.  These compounds may ultimately be utilized in the synthesis of  new pharmaceuticals, and as catalysts for the preparation of  polymers.  ***
